{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a405b5ff-0fab-4766-86ca-e9aaf54efc66","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but it depends on `Domain.fs` types.\n\nFixing by reordering `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01E8kHG4iL4qyxocw6Fns7rq","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-902634591505440fa75fe22ac71c36b2/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-902634591505440fa75fe22ac71c36b2/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"90f4a18d-ce02-4dbe-8a73-3f826b02ae38","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — references `BrokenOrder.Domain`, but `Domain.fs` hasn't been compiled yet\n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nThe fix is to put `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs`.","outputTokens":361,"requestId":"C784:3250B5:1571C0:1C1B00:69FFD73C"},"id":"40736af0-e4f0-4364-ac68-7db7bdfbf9e3","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:54:26.593Z","parentId":"16899622-5001-4de9-994b-50f6a1f8adf0"}
